  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in Senate",
    "asOf": "2022-09-29",
    "date": "2023-08-21T18:45:31Z",
    "text": "Protect Student Borrowers Act of 2022\n\nThis bill requires institutions of higher education (IHEs) participating in the William D. Ford Federal Direct Loan program to accept specified risk-sharing requirements for defaulted student loans, which shall include requiring certain IHEs to make payments to address the risk of such defaults. The bill also establishes in the Treasury a separate account for the deposit of such risk-sharing payments."
